    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And Jesus asked him, saying, what is thy name?.... This question was put, not out of ignorance in Christ, but for the sake of those that were with him; and partly, that the miserable condition of this man might be the more known; and partly, that his own power might be the more manifest in the dispossession: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and he said, legion, because many devils were entered into him; See Gill on Mark 5:9. ",
