  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Cambridge Bible for Schools and Colleges",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "30",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "What is thy name?",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] The question was no doubt asked in mercy. Gently to ask a person’s name is often an effectual way to calm the agitations and fix the wavering thoughts of these sufferers.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And he said, Legion",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] A legion consisted of 6000 soldiers, and this man (who was probably a Jew) would have become familiar with the name since the Roman conquest of Palestine. The ancient Megiddo was now called Legio, still ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Ledjun.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " The answer shewed how wildly perturbed was the man’s spirit, and how complete was the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "duality",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of his consciousness. He could not distinguish between himself and the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "multitudes",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of demons by whom he believed himself to be possessed. His individuality was lost in demoniac hallucinations.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
